$y_1=\cos \left(m \sin ^{-1} x\right) \cdot \frac{m}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \sqrt{1-x^2} y_1=m \cos \left(m \sin ^{-1} x\right) \\
& \Rightarrow\left(1-x^2\right) y_2-x y_1+m^2 y=0 \\
& {\left[\left(1-x^2\right) y_{n+2}+n(-2 x) y_{n+1}+\frac{n(n-1)}{2}(-2) y_n\right]-\left[x y_{n+1}+n \cdot 1 \cdot y_n\right]+m^2 y_n=0}
\end{aligned}
$$
Simplifying we get, $\left(1-x^2\right) y_{n+2}-(2 n+1) y_{n+1}-\left(n^2-m^2\right) y_n=0$
